{
  "texts": [
    "Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) involve two neural networks (i.e., generator and the discriminator) in a competitive framework to generate highly authentic synthetic data.",
    "The generator constructs data instances, which the discriminator appraises for genuineness.",
    "This adversarial training iteratively refines the quality of generator's output, progressively matching it to the distribution of the real-world instances.",
    "GANs have significantly impacted areas such as medical imaging and art generation.",
    "In medical imaging, GANs generate synthetic yet realistic images of X-rays and MRIs, facilitating the training of diagnostic models without breaching patient confidentiality."
  ]
}